				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">GradualGames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What could cause an unpaired write except for improper locking of nmi vs. main thread?</div><br />I can't think of many things... Even improper locking would still execute an even amount of $2005/6 writes, so the latch would remain consistent afterwards, even if those specific writes we're botched.<br /><br />One thing I can think of are mid-screen horizontal scroll changes... I seem to remember some games not bothering to do a second $2005 write since they only needed to change the X scroll, so this could end up resulting in an inconsistent state of the latch.</div>

